http://purl.org/dc/terms/description.@value: Xhosa Beadwork Ontology (XBO) is a knowledge representation with a perspective on preservation, promotion, development and management of IK on Xhosa Beadwork. Hence, this ontology creates a common conceptual framework for beadwork using common beadwork knowledge described within Xhosa Beadwork. XBO is anchored on personal ornamentation function of Xhosa Beadwork. The ontology combines many aspects of the associated description of Xhosa Beadwork in order to give a rich classification. This description of Xhosa Beadwork is captured with value partitions and restrictions on beadwork classes. Then a series of defined classes establishes the classification. XBO describes the characteristics of an array of Xhosa Beadwork viz; Headband, Necklace, Armlet, Bracelet, Waistband and Anklet.

http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#com.@value: Age  is a  ValuePartition that describes only values from  subclasses Infanthood, Adolescence, Childhood or Adulthood . NB These subclasses can themselves be further partitioned.
The class  Anklet is used for concepts that represent a beadwork Item in form of a  string or band or ring worn around the Ankle.
The class  Armlet is used to represent a beadwork Item  in form of a string or band or ring worn around the Upper Arm or  high on the Arm
Class  BeadworkEntity comprise concepts that represent objects or items of beadwork and the associated description of the item with respect to the accepted statues of Xhosa Beadwork.
BodyRegion is a  ValuePartition that describes only values from  subclasses Neck, Waist, Arm, Shin, Head, Ankle or Wrist. NB These subclasses can themselves be further partitioned.
BodyType is a  ValuePartition that describes only values from  subclasses  Flexible  or Inflexible. NB These subclasses can themselves be further partitioned.
The class Bracelet represent an article or beadwork Item in form of a loop or band encircling or worn around the Wrist.
Colour is a  ValuePartition that describes only values from  subclasses Primary, Secondary or Tertiary. NB These subclasses can themselves be further partitioned.
Decoration is a  ValuePartition that describes only values from  subclasses Tab, Tassel, Streamer, Strand, Charm or Fringe. NB These subclasses can themselves be further partitioned.

The entire Xhosa Beadwork Ontology (XBO) is underneath DomainEntity. We use DomainEntity for  housekeeping, to manage the routine tasks that must be done in order for efficient  modelling and XBO functioning i.e. as a common super class in case of a property with multiple domains or ranges.
The class Headband designates a beadwork Item or band or narrow strip worn  around the Head.
Item is used for concepts that represent a tangible or physical visible Item of beadwork either as a collection or as a single Item of beadwork.
Material is a  ValuePartition that describes only values from  subclasses Natural or Synthetic. NB These subclasses can themselves be further partitioned.
The class Necklace is used represent a beadwork  Item in form of  a band or string  that is worn around the Neck.

The class Person contains concepts that denote a human being, regarded as an individual in the physical commonsense intuition and according to the law as the subject of rights and duties as recognized by a culture or country.
Class PersonEntity comprise concepts that represent a Person and the associated description of a Person as recognized by the law or the accepted precepts of a culture.
Position is a  ValuePartition that describes only values from  subclasses Upper, Middle or Lower. NB These subclasses can themselves be further partitioned.
Quantity is a  ValuePartition that describes only values from  subclasses Single, Double or Multi. NB These subclasses can themselves be further partitioned.
Rank is a  ValuePartition that describes only values from  subclasses Royal, Noble or Common. NB These subclasses can themselves be further partitioned.
Sex is a  ValuePartition that describes only values from  subclasses Male or Female. NB These subclasses can themselves be further partitioned.
Side is a  ValuePartition that describes only values from  subclasses LeftSide or RightSide. NB These subclasses can themselves be further partitioned.
Size  is a  ValuePartition that describes only values from  subclasses Small, Medium or Large. NB These subclasses can themselves be further partitioned.
Tribe is a  ValuePartition that describes only values from  subclasses Xhosa, Pondo, Fengu, Bhaca, Bomvana or Thembu. NB These subclasses can themselves be further partitioned.
Use is a  ValuePartition that describes only values from  subclasses Ritual or Ceremony. NB These subclasses can themselves be further partitioned.

ValuePartition is a pattern that describes a restricted set of classes from which a property can be associated. The parent class is used in restrictions, and the covering axiom means that only members of the subclasses may be used as values.  ValuePartition  has subclasses  Material, Colour, Rank, BodyType, Sex, Tribe, Size, Age, Use, Position, BodyRegion, Decoration, Side and Quantity.
The class Waistband represents a beadwork Item inform of  a strip or band encircling or  fitting around the Waist.
Specific Age group value of a Person or suitable age group value intended for an Item.

Relates a Person or Item and the required  Age  group associated with the use of Item. hasAgeGroup specifies the Age interval or range for which the Item or Person is valid. This allows specifying that a certain  Item is valid only for a certain Age group.
Relates Item to the type of body that the Item is equipped with as determined in the entity ItemBody.
Relates a Person to another Person (object) who is a child of that Person.
Relates an Item to the presence of Colour in the makeup or content of an Item.
Relates a specific elaborate design feature or theme of Decoration to an Item.
Associates a Person to another Person who is the biological Father of that Person.
Associates an Item to a type of underlying physical Material used to make or is incorporated in the Item.
Relates a Person to another Person who is the biological Mother of that Person.
Associates  a Person (object)  to another to another Person who is a parent of that Person.
Associates the Item with the recommended Position that denotes a point within some BodyRegion where the Item is intended to occupy or be placed or worn.

Associates an Item with a unit of measure Quantity, where Quantity is how much or proportion there is of an Item, Colour or Material. For example, this allows specifying that a certain Quantity is valid only for a certain Item.
Relates a Person or Item to the appropriate type of level or rank or status held by a Person or Item according to classifications or social structure defined in Rank.
Links a Person or Item to the values Male or Female  describing Sex. Person or Item is related to an instance of Sex.
Relates an Item to the Side on which to put the Item relative to a centre or reference location such as the trunk of the human body.
Associates the physical magnitude or dimensions used to represent an Item to Size.
Associates a Person to another Person in a shared activity of common interest such as a partnership of traditional marriage or common law marriage or  civil union.
Associates an Item or Person to a Tribe meaning a group or social division of people an Item or Person belongs to. Tribe is a characteristic such as Thembu, Pondo or Bomvana.
Relates an Item or Person to the appropriate or recommended category of Use for which the Item is intended.
Links the Item to the recommended  Person for whom the Item is considered suitable or  eligible  Age to adorn or wear  or put on the   Item.
Associates an Item with a particular  place, location or region of the human body occupied by an Item as represented in BodyRegion.
